<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98340724280462></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98340724280462><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=12&mid=98340724280462>RE: Mage PvP</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 28th 7:40 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The last posts were very good ones.  I play both a mage and a druid on Tallon and have pvped both.  The biggest problem a mage can deal with on a druid is his speed spells, evac, and if he has a chance to charm an animal.  If he charms an animal you will have the same problem he has, dealing with two opponents.  The pet and the caster.  Some of the druids I have found however don't have their expulse spell memmed in a slot favoring other spells which definitely puts them at a disadvantage.  The problem with a mage is that if the fight goes bad they don't have anything to get them out of the situation quickly except for gate and that has a long cast time.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98336204472336></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98336204472336><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=12&mid=98336204472336>RE: Mage PvP</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>363 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 28th 7:07 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well if you are fighting other magic users you will definately want an air pet. If you are up against a smart enchanter, you will probably die no matter what you do anyway. They will charm your pet and have it attack you. Anyway, your best bet is to send your air pet on the chanter, and then blast from bolt range. If they charm your pet, you probably will die. However, you can try to nuke them dead before they can charm your pet and send it at you. Enchanters DO get damage shields, so its a bit hard to do.<br><br>If you are up against a necro your best bet is to send your air pet in, and then run to the max distance of the range that your bolt spell has, and start blasting from far, far away. To outrun another player, or even a monster(if you have at least 2 bubbles of health), hold down the Ctrl key and the left or right movement key while running. The effect is that you will strafe while running, which will let you outrun some monsters and players if your health is at 2 bubbles or more.<br><br>If you are up against a wizard you should pretty much just send your air pet in and nuke. At higher levels wizards can be horrible opponents, however. They will root your pet, then chain stun/DD you until you are dead. If anything goes wrong they can just cast shadow step as much as the need to. It only costs 10 mana and has a cast time of 1 second, so it gets them out of bad situations. Plus, wizards have damage shields and magicians don't, so that gives them even more of an edge. <br><br>In my opinion, magicians are actually the WORST dueling class of the pure casters. ALL of the other casters get damage shields, which help out a bunch. All of the other casters also get root spells to make your pet useless. In addition to that all of the other casters get fear and/or stun spells which will screw you over.<br><br>Magicians are very good at dueling during the newbie levels, and they are pretty good at the higher levels, but they definately can't do as well as many other classes. And not just pure casters either. Shadowknights and Bards can kick a magicians butt too.<br><br>But fear not, magicians are still a great class! I still love them, dueling isn't everything,<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
